Friday August 23rd 2013 3:12 pm -04:00,Also if you want to execute a Python3 source file without having to write python you can add a shebang! line at the beginning of the file:File program.py:#!/usr/bin/env python3  print(Greetings overlord.)    And then use the command chmod +x program.py to turn it into an executable file.    Now you can run the program with the command: ./program.pyouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop$ chmod +x program.py  ouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop$ ./program.pyGreetings overlord.ouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop$    If you need to use a function that is in another file named lets say module.py then you can use the import statement:    from module import *  this is roughly equivalent to using IDLEs Run module menu command:     Files in the directory    ouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop/PyTest$ ls -Fmodule.py program.py*module.pydef f(x):    return x ** 2x = 9program.py#!/usr/bin/env python3from module import *print(Greetings overlord. f(4) f(x))    Result:    ouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop/PyTest$ ./program.pyGreetings overlord. 16 81ouroumov@Adcap:~/Desktop/PyTest$ , Pinned Approved Resolved,3
