Tuesday August 20th 2013 3:43 am -04:00,Yeah it is a question of memory but I dont think it relates to the garbage collector.  Instead I believe that the id() function looks up the address of the object referred to by the variable because the object can exist even if it is not assigned to a variable.  Heres an interesting snippet to illustrate:  >>> hex(id(4))0x8bb9e0>>> x = 4>>> hex(id(x))0x8bb9e0>>> hex(id(4))0x8bb9e0, Resolved,6
