Thursday August 22nd 2013 6:06 am -04:00,In any case do not be afraid to ask a questionPeople in the course staff are a really nice bunch and there is a boatload of students here that made it their mission in life to help others.   What follow is only some suggestions on how to ask for help. Step 1 - Ask a RoBoT      (Search the forum)Common practice on the Internet.With over 65 000 students (and counting) registered for this course it is likely that someone ran into the same problem so take a few minutes to search the forums using keywords and Check the FAQ.Step 2 - Choose where to askIf you dont want to ask in English or if you feel like you can express your problem better in your native tongueConsider asking in a language-specific study group.The Arabic Study Group. اذا احتجتم للمساعدة، تعالوا واسألوا هناThe Dutch Study Group. Als je hulp nodig hebt vraag het hier.The Spanish Study Group. Si necesitas ayuda preguntanos aquí.The German Study Group. Wenn Ihr Hilfe braucht fragt uns hier.The Chinese Study Group. 如果有任何問題歡迎到這裡發問！-- 如果有任何问题欢迎到这里发问！The French-Speaking Study group. Si vous avez besoin daide venez demander ici !The Russian Study Group. Если вам нужна помощь задавайте свои вопросы здесь.The Italian Study Group. Se vi serve aiuto chiedete qui!The Brazilian Study Group. Se você precisa de ajuda venha e nós pergunte aqui.  If you decide to ask in English choose the right sub-forum.       The forums here have a lot of sections and sub-sections each with its own purpose.  If you prefer Facebook You can also get help on the official Facebook Study Group.Step 3 - Watch out for the special case of the [Platform Problem]If you can determine that your problem is of such nature (because its obvious because nobody could help you because someone told you so because you tried everything else etc...) then you dont have a lot of choices left but if you are very motivated you can submit a bug report.Here is a real live example of a problem another student encountered in which I explain in detail the process of submitting such a report. Step 4 - Choose a meaningful title that will also help competent people notice the threadIt is generally better to start a new thread rather than posting in an existing one that way your question will be more visible than if you post in a slightly related thread with a lot of comments.If you have a coding problem then a lot of students will be able to help you but if your issue appears to be related to your environment (Example: you have trouble installing IDLE) then mentioning the Operating System you use (Windows OSX Linux flavor etc) is a good idea.I am totally useless when it comes to Apple computers or Windows 8. Step 5 - Describe the issue in detailsGive some context explain how you got there.If the problem is related to a video lecture say which one.If it is a programming issue then give some code using code blocks.If youre not sure where in the code is the error give all your code using a pastebin-type website such as the Debian Pastebin.  Take care of not breaching the Honor Code when the coding problem concerns the graded Exercises / Assignments.  Its OK to post code that you know dont workIts not OK to post code that worksYou can also think about posting links to screen captures of the bug in action using a picture hosting site such as imm.io  Step 6 - Post your question and check for an answer after 5 minutesThe course forum is a very active place.Sometime you will get an answer or a request for additional details literally in seconds. Step 7 - [The end]: post to say if / when your problem is solvedThat way people who helped you can move on to helping others.If you started a new thread to post your question please mark it as resolved.[Notice: this is a work in progress]  , Pinned Approved,22
