Thursday August 22nd 2013 6:28 am -04:00,Why is 0.3 * 3 equal to 0.8999999999999999? Thats just wrong!Well the other way to think about it is that its extremely close to be true.  This is a   /!\ complex topic /!\   that involves the way floating point numbers are represented in memory.  This is not specific to Python you will see the same kind of things in many languages.If youre really curious you can check out the official explanation of the Python FAQ., Pinned Locked,0
Thursday August 22nd 2013 6:54 am -04:00,How is a parameter different from an argument?A parameter is a variable that appears between the parentheses in a function header and an argument is an expression that appears between the parentheses of a function call.>>> def area(base height):        # <-- Here base and height are parameters....     return base * height / 2... >>> h = 4>>> area(3 h)                     # <-- Here area is called with the arguments 3 and h.6.0, Pinned Locked,0
Thursday August 22nd 2013 7:38 pm -04:00,Why do I get a SyntaxError when I try to define a function?Thats probably because you forgot to add a new empty line after you finished writing the function body.Here are the important points:>>> def f(x):          # <-- Dont forget the colon at the end!...     return x ** 2  # <-- Dont forget to indent this line with four spaces left of return!...                    # <-- Leave this line empty!>>> f(4)    # <-- Now you can call the function!16, Pinned Locked,0
