Thursday September 5th 2013 11:16 am -04:00,Hello AgnieszkaSure Im gonna tell you why I would recommend Python over Java for an introductory programming course please keep in mind that this is my own personal opinion though not a concerted answer from the course staff.  1 - Python allows for quick experimentation and therefore is Fun.With a capital F.  Being an interpreted language you dont have to perform a compile step when you want to run a program so you can change your code and execute it right away.That reduces the chance of modifications to the code not being reflected at execution time I cant tell you how many times I forgot to recompile a Java or C++ program and didnt immediately understood what I did wrong.The fact that you can use it as a quick and dirty calculator is also most helpful when in the classroom. 2 - Python has a very rich standard library and is easy to useIt allows the user to do a great deal of things without always having to rely on third party libraries.It is also ideal to build quick and dirty tools that will make your life easier.I use it (amongst other things) to create the PDF versions of the in-video quizzes each week.I described some parts of the process here.  3 - Python removes the need for the user to constantly worry about resources managementMemory allocation is a very important thing to understand when youre a full blown CS major but for most users that just want to have fun writing small and non-critical programs this is an added layer of complexity that is not strictly necessary.  4 - Python is beautiful forces good programming habits onto beginners and the documentation process is supported by its designMy personal favorite.There is a lot of cool things in the Python syntax.That makes for easy-to-read code both for teachers evaluating homework and for students reading example code.The control of the logic flow is done through indentation and thats very useful I went into some details about that here.  Im sure theres a lot of other valid reasons to use Python but those are the main selling points for me and thats why yes without a doubt I would recommend Python over Java for an introductory course. Cheers , Pinned Approved Resolved,11
