Sunday August 25th 2013 5:56 pm -04:00,When you assign a variable to another its not the address of the variable that becomes the value for the new variable but instead its the value referred to by the first variable.  Heres an illustrative snippet:  >>> Tree = 4>>> hex(id(Tree))       # Tree contains that address0x8bb9e0>>> Forest = 7>>> hex(id(Forest))     # Forest contains that address0x8bba40>>> Forest = Tree>>> hex(id(Forest))     # Now Forest contains the address that that was previously in Tree0x8bb9e0>>> Forest4>>> Tree = 8>>> Forest4, Unresolved,0
