ll recursively help us recruit more members.Stuff you can do if you can come on the IRC channel:Drop me a line in private when needed. 1 - Hunt down FAQ items.We are currently late in setting up the Week 2 FAQ. Well start working on it but any help is welcomed. 2 - If you stumble upon Honor Code violations alert us so we can edit the posts.If Im not connected or afk you can alert nitish` or d4vey if you see them. The guidelines about posting code samples or attempted answers for the Exercises or Assignments are as follow:If someone posts an answer / code that he knows is right then thats a problem and you can alert us / notify the poster.If someone posts an answer / code that is wrong then thats not a problem.If someone posts an answer / code that he think is wrong but isnt thats a problem too and you can alert us / notify the poster.If someone after seeing a wrong answer posts some helpful advice without giving the answer such as Please be careful what operator you choose to use thats not a problem.If someone after seeing a wrong answer posts something like Just replace / with // and thats right then thats a problem too and you should either alert us or notify the poster.    I know this is a fuzzy line but please use your best judgment. , Approved,2
