Saturday August 31st 2013 3:45 am -04:00,Hi Jonny Gary There is also a print as you go way to solve this problem in Python 2.for i in range(1 8):    for j in range(1 8):        print i * j    printAnd to output the result to a file:file = open(file.txt w)for i in range(1 8):    for j in range(1 8):        print >> file i * j    print >> filefile.close()Using Python 3 you can use the end =  keyword argument of the print function.Cheers,None,0
