Saturday August 31st 2013 7:46 am -04:00,doctest is a standard Python module. (Well see modules next week.)  It is used to test the examples you write in the documentation strings for a function.  __name__ is a variable that is automatically set and is equal to __main__ only when you execute a module not when you import it from another module.  This might be obscure but next weeks videos will help you understand the module stuff somewhat.  Cheers, Resolved,0
