Saturday August 31st 2013 1:05 pm -04:00,Hello Lebbe  The absence of output from the shell is normal when you do an assignment statement.  Nothing is printed because the variable is made to point to the value:  >>> sunny_greeting = What a beautiful day!>>> sunny_greeting  # Once the assignment is done you can show the value like that.What a beautiful day!>>> Now for the other problem: this is because you have used Double Single Quotes instead of Double Quotes in your expression.  sunny_greeting = What a beautiful day!This is different from:sunny_greeting = What a beautiful day!Protip: always use code blocks in your posts when you have to show code.  Cheers, Resolved,0
