Sunday September 1st 2013 5:01 am -04:00,Its probably because you used some weird-looking characters instead of quotes signs.  Did you type that in a word-processing program?  You need a simple text editor to write code such as IDLEs editor or NotePad++ if youre running Windows OS.  To clarify your code is like this:def convert_to_celsius(fahrenheit):    ´´´(number) -> number    Return the number of Celsius degrees equivalent to fahrenheit    >>> convert_to_celsius(32)    0    >>> convert_to_celsius(212)    100    ´´´    return fahrenheit - 32 * 5 / 9But it should be like this:def convert_to_celsius(fahrenheit):    (number) -> number    Return the number of Celsius degrees equivalent to fahrenheit    >>> convert_to_celsius(32)    0    >>> convert_to_celsius(212)    100        return fahrenheit - 32 * 5 / 9Cheers, Resolved,0
