Saturday September 7th 2013 11:07 pm -04:00,Thats how you exit a logic block in Python: you break indentation to return to the previous indentation level. Here the previous indentation level was the one inside the functions body where the if keyword was placed. For the same reason you can write multiple function definition in a given file by breaking indentation and returning to the first character on the left of the line thus exiting the functions body., Unresolved,0
