Saturday September 14th 2013 12:30 am -04:00,Try and think about this the way a normal human - not a program would.  A human would look at every character in the string more or less one by one and say the sequence is not valid as soon as he sees an illegal character if he cant find an illegal character in the string he would say the sequence is valid.  In near pseudo code the same thing can be described like this:  # For each character in the sequence...    # ...check if the character is illegal and if it is:        # say the sequence is illegal and stop.# Youve now reached the end of the sequence without stopping: say the sequence is legal.Now you can transcribe that into Python code and it will work., Unresolved,28
