Wednesday September 25th 2013 10:42 pm -04:00,Well when Python evaluates a boolean expression the last thing evaluated becomes the value of that expression. >>> True and TT>>> False and TFalse>>> False or TTRecall the rules for evaluating boolean expressions:     From left to right    and binds more strongly than or. (It has higher precedence)                If the left hand side of an and expression is False the right hand side is not evaluated    The right hand side of an or expression is only evaluated if the left hand side is False.And theres an extra rule: if a string shows up in place of a boolean value its considered False if its the empty string  and True if its not.So in the code nuc == A and T  if the left hand side is True because its an and operator the right hand side is evaluated its value is T so it becomes the value for the expression and because what followsis the right hand side of an or expression its not evaluated. However if nuc is not equal to A then the whole and expression evaluates to False and the right hand side of the or expressionis then evaluated etc..., Pinned Approved Resolved,2
